# Basic LAN Connectivity
## Objective
To establish communication between two PCs connected in the same Local Area Network (LAN) using a switch.

## Description
This lab demonstrates basic LAN setup in Cisco Packet Tracer. Two PCs are connected through a switch and assigned IP addresses in the same network. Connectivity is verified using the `ping` command.

## Devices Used
- 2 PCs
- 1 Switch
- Copper straight-through cables

## Concepts Covered
- Basic LAN setup
- IP addressing
- Same network communication
- End-to-end connectivity testing

## IP Addressing
| Device | Interface | IP Address | Subnet Mask |
|--------|-----------|------------|-------------|
| PC1    | NIC       | 192.168.1.10 | 255.255.255.0 |
| PC2    | NIC       | 192.168.1.20 | 255.255.255.0 |

## Steps Performed
1. Added two PCs and one switch in Packet Tracer.
2. Connected both PCs to the switch using copper straight-through cables.
3. Assigned IP addresses to both PCs.
4. Verified connectivity using the `ping` command.

## Verification
- Successful ping from PC1 to PC2
- Successful ping from PC2 to PC1

## Files Included
- `connect-2-pcs.pkt` → Packet Tracer simulation file
- `screenshots/` → topology and ping verification images

## Result
Both PCs were able to communicate successfully within the same LAN.

## Conclusion
This lab helps in understanding the basic working of a LAN, IP addressing, and connectivity verification between devices in the same network.
